    "body": "Just a note that  due to `npm` not supporting installation from a subfolder (in this case /contracts for the `@openzeppelin/contracts` package what's the best way to plug this in without changing the import declarations in our contracts? `npm install https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts.git#solc-0.7 --save` only updates the `openzeppelin-solidity` package. Only way I see right now is to publish own package, e.g. `@openzeppelin-argent/contracts` and switch imports. Can you think of a better way?",
